Oct 8 2009 	I keep returning to the Majestic	It's the oldest hotel in SF (the only one that survived the Great Earthquake &amp; Fire) and it does show its age -- but I kind of like its slightly shabby elegance. It really feels like San Francisco. It has pretty much none -- repeat: none -- of the conveniences and services of a fully modern hotel. No room service, a restaurant that has been closed pretty often, no armies of uniformed staff. (Although they have gotten the free WiFi working pretty well.) But the staff is usually pretty friendly and helpful (in an informal laid-back SF way). The rooms are large (try a junior suite) and the prices are reasonable.	
