Mar 12 2008 	Edwardian Elegance 	What a wonderful experience at the Hotel Majestic. The building's facade is impeccable with ornate Edwardian architecture with an inviting doorstep. Check-in was a breeze and I was directed to a charming, frescoed elevator. I stayed in a 'standard' room, but there wasn't anything standard about it. As a graduate from the University of Virginia, I love old-world architecture and attention to detail, and that's what I found in my room: canopy bed, fireplace, large antique wardrobe, comfy chair and spotless bathroom. The curtains and fabrics made me feel I was in another era, and at the same time, it wasn't overwhelming, as what can easily happen to decorating gone awry. The side tables could use a new coat of varnish, it looked a little tired, but that's really all I can comment on the negative.The clawfoot tub was a nice touch, but it can be dangerous entering and exiting. I know they want character, but maybe they should add a step; the elderly or those with bad knees would be at a disadvantage. There is a handle bar on the wall to aid in this, however. The maid service was excellent, all items replenished and wastebaskets emptied. On my last day, the concierge and doorman recommended an excellent restaurant for breakfast (one that had adequate space for small luggage so I didn't feel crammed in). When I asked a question on where to get a MUNI pass, they more than obliged the nearest place, and I was always met with a smile.I did have breakfast in the restaurant, but the menu was quite limited and more than I wanted to spend (egg/pancakes for $15), so I had fruit/yogurt combo. Again, the waitstaff was attentive and pleasant. The only unpleasant person I encountered was the bartender one night; even though he liked to engage in conversation, his tone was judgemental and quite critical of the clubs and bars I wanted to patronize later that evening. Rather than suggesting a range of options, he seemed quite keen on saying how awful the club I wanted to go to was. I wanted to see the DJ, and went on my merry way, and where, by the way, I had a fantastic time dancing.I would certainly return to Hotel Majestic; I like the idea of a neighborhood hotel rather than one by Fisherman's Wharf or downtown. Just get a MUNI pass, the buses 2 and 3 will get you anywhere across town or at least to another major busline where you need to go.	
