Feb 19 2006	Quiet and with character	Stayed at the Hotel Majestic because it was suggested by the hotel where I customarily stay when it was all booked up. Staying at the Majestic feels like staying at some friend's rich uncle's mansion when they are away. It is an older building with &quot;character,&quot; meaning that the elevator has inexplicable pictures of monkeys playing and in the room are canopied beds where they canopies get in your way. However, you have to love a place where the hot and cold faucets are labelled &quot;Hot&quot; and &quot;Cold.&quot; The service is top notch - super friendly, able, and willing to help out the guests, most of whom appear to be return customers.The Majestic is a little out of the beaten path, but that's a good thing if you want some quiet. And, the 2,3, and 4 MUNI buses stop practically at its doorstep with the downtown loop only 2 blocks away. Japantown is only 3 blocks away and a really excellent supermarket is 1.5 blocks away (w/ really good empenadas).The only minus is if you have a car they don't have a convenient mechanism for stowing and retrieving it. Also, as of early Feb when I was there, the bar and restaurant were being renovated, but the complimentary continental breakfast was first rate with good coffee. Major renovations are due to begin in earnest soon. No question, I would definitely stay here again if my regular place was sold out again, if for nothing more than to get the empenadas at the local grocery.	
