Mar 7 2005	Depends on what you are looking for	I was looking for a romantic hotel in SF that was away from the hustle and bustle but close enough so we could walk to places of interest. The Majestic did not disappoint. It is a very romantic hotel, old and grand in its history and decor. The service was very friendly and accommodating. If you don’t like to walk and don’t want to cab to places of interest, then the Majestic is not for you. If you want to fall in love, or are in love, and want to stroll hand in hand down SF streets on your way to Union Square or the Warf and then be able to retreat from the crowds, then let me recommend the Majestic. The only downsides of the Majestic are that the furnishings are a bit worn and the shower was disappointing. The former should be expected from such an old hotel and the later is only an issue if you like to take romantic showers with the one you love.	
Feb 15 2005	Very nice quiet location	My husband and I stayed at the Majestic and found it to be a very nice &amp; clean place to stay with alot of character. If you're looking for something different than the white boxy room with standard run of the mill motel decor, then you'll find it here, along with great prices and a very quiet location. The Majestic is a couple of blocks up the street from Japan Town, which if you're familiar with San Francisco, is a very quiet, peaceful &amp; safe area. No panhandlers here. It's close enough to Fillmore Street shopping, and walkable to several area restaurants (if you don't mind a few block walk). The weekend we stayed, there was an above average continental breakfast, but if you want a full breakfast, there's the Cafe Mum or Denny's a couple of blocks away. The on-site restaurant advertised is closed, and hopefully they'll find someone to take it over before too long, as it would be a nice attribute.And if you're looking for a nice, quiet, uncrowded bar, there is a very small bar in the hotel called the Avalon, where they serve yummy huckleberry cosmos and lemon drops that are absolutely delicious. Perfect for a romantic drink for you and your date!! (Altho we went on Valentine's weekend and the bar was full, we've gone other weekends and it was less crowded)We've tried several small boutique and European hotels in SF, and the Majestic is one of our favorites. The cost is very reasonable, but don't book there if you want fancy smanchy. Our room was small but adequate, probably because we asked for the least expensive room. We'd definately stay there again, and probably get a suite next time.	
Jan 24 2005	disappointed	you can't argue with the price in a very pricey city but be aware of a few things: 1) This hotel is NOT in Pacific Heights! 2) Quiet is an understatement - if this hotel were a person we would pronounce it dead. 3) you will have to drive EVERYWHERE - because the hotel is hell and gone from ANYWHERE 4) The small room is, well ... small. I couldn't blow dry my hair withhout hitting the door with my brush (don't you just hate that).All in all ... stay at the MAX.	
Jan 20 2005	Really enjoyed this one	I really enjoyed staying at this hotel. I was very appreciative for the comments that everyone else left because the first thing I did when I got to the hotel was ask for a quiet room with a great hotel. I didn't get a fireplace that I read about nor did I get one of those nice bathtubs, but who cares? I wouldn't bathe in one of those anywhere except in my home! (I get grossed out fast by bacteria.) I ended up on the fifth floor with a great view of San Francisco.Staff: The staff was impeccable. Even the maids were nice and polite in a very traditional and professional way. The front desk help was friendly and even the man that delivered for room service was excellent and extremely professional. I liked him and made sure to tip him extra for his great service.Cleanliness: It was very clean, but I would give it 3 stars in this area because it didn't LOOK clean because the hotel is getting older. I'm sorry, but there was a big stain on the carpet in the room I was in. But I feel confident that everything WAS clean, it just looked a bit run down.Ambiance: The location is perfect because it is quiet and quaint and away from all the noise. The lobby is beautiful as is where breakfast is served (i had a wonderful wonderful time eating breakfast every morning, it was so relaxing and their free continental breakfast was more than adequate). The rooms themselves are very very nice, but old.... and getting a bit run down. But each room is different and another one I looked into did not look run down at all.I would stay here again for sure but next time I am going to get a suite, since they are SO much nicer. I loved my time here!	
